Generalised #Layer2 solutions behave like #Ethereum but faster and cheaper, e.g. #Arbitrum #Optimism and #Metis. 

Application based solutions focus on a specific use case, e.g. #dYdX which is a high throughput exchange. 9/12

Benefits! Lower fees - tx are bundles off chain reducing on chain #Ethereum tx fees making it more affordable for more people.

New applications - faster throughput and finality offer the scope for new applications and better user experience. 8/12

The preferred #Layer2 solution is via rollups. They bundle hundreds of txs into a single #Layer1 tx.

The tx are executed outside of #Ethereum but the data is posted to the main chain ensuring security and finality. 6/12

This enables #ETH to do what it's good at settling transaction in a decentralized and secure manner.

Whilst allowing #Layer2 to handle the workload of an increased number of faster and cheaper transactions. 5/12

#Layer2 solutions attempt solve the scalability (speed/cost) challenge whilst maintaining decentralization and security

They are separate #blockchains that extend #Ethereum whilst inheriting the security guarantees. 4/12
